1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Coding agents are good at adding rules, memories, skills, and tools.
But accumulation is not improvement, and old interventions rarely remove themselves.

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Codex Metabolism gives Codex collaboration a finite maintenance loop:
observe recurring friction, adopt the smallest useful fix, evaluate it on later sessions, and prune what no longer helps.

3
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:45,000
We built the core with Codex and GPT-5.6.
It helped inspect real session formats, separate evidence from inference, search existing tools first, and work from failing tests.

4
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:00,000
This public demo uses only synthetic sessions.
Two sessions repeat a failed deployment, user correction, and verified recovery. No private data is read.

5
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:18,000
One zero-install command runs the first review.
It stages four evidence-backed decisions, including CREATE HARNESS for mechanical prevention and PATCH RULE for the bounded managed region in AGENTS.md.

6
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Before creating anything, the router climbs five rungs:
necessity, Codex built-ins, installed capabilities, repository assets, and reviewed open-source tools. An unchecked rung blocks creation.

7
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Review never mutates live state.
The hook begins as pending trust, only the marked AGENTS.md region is patchable, and every approved change receives a reversible receipt.

8
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:12,000
The isolated demo then adds two later successful sessions and reviews again.
The result is KEEP HARNESS, VALIDATED. Its active receipt also prevents Codex Metabolism from proposing the same fix again.

9
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:29,000
The same review keeps a useful skill and marks an old unused skill as a retirement candidate only when lifecycle evidence is complete.
Retirement is human-approved, archived, and restorable—never silent deletion.

10
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Existing tools come before new code and are never auto-installed.
An optional GPT-5.6 advisor adds a bounded second opinion without overriding deterministic gates.

11
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Codex Metabolism improves collaboration:
observe, adopt, evaluate, and prune.
